{"key":"post-12512918","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12512918</id>\n<content>I've found little difference really between shaking immediately and waiting two or three days.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;My argument for not shaking for a couple of days is based on not disturbing the mycelium that is growing on the wedge.&amp;nbsp; Let it grow off into the grains.&amp;nbsp; When you shake immediately, it disturbs that mycelium, but it doesn't seem to 'rub off' the wedge and into the grains.&amp;nbsp; You still have to wait for the wedge to recover and grow into the grains.&amp;nbsp; Thus you gain a day or two by waiting to shake.&amp;nbsp; It's splitting hairs for sure, but in my experience the hair-splitting is in favor of waiting.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>12512916</prev>\n<first>12512844</first>\n<last>12512918</last>\n<when>1273110999</when>\n<utime>05/06/10 04:56 AM</utime>\n</post>"}